metadata.name: Eyeball Cracked Egg
metadata.description:
Can you see it? It’s transparent but smells like yellow, sensations where we come from and can’t see with our eyes, a corner where it can be just what it is. 

This is a metaphor for reducing to the essential, returning to nature where we come from, which is part of the universe's composition. If we see where we come from can we know where we are going?
